<title>UK: Abbey National down in weak bank sector.</title>
<headline>Abbey National down in weak bank sector.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Abbey National Plc were the biggest decliners in the FTSE 100 index by late afternoon on Tuesday as bid hopes faded and the bank sector continued to be buffeted by profit-taking, dealers said.</p>
<p>Abbey shares were down 42p or 4.8 percent at 826-1/2p by 1346 GMT in volume of 3.9 million shares, after earlier dropping as low as 815p.</p>
